the gym hasn’t been easy, but it is a journey that i’ve been absolutely in love with 🤍

i try to go to the gym at least 5x a week. i’m really focused on getting in my protein and trying to stay in a deficit. it’s been about a month and i feel so much lighter. there are days where it gets challenging but my biggest advice is to keep showing up for YOU. build up to it and don’t do it all at once because you will dread doing it. start 10mins a day.. then 15.. then 30.. etc. small changes babes will make an impact. don’t think you have to be perfect from the start 🤍

WE DID IT!! 🥹🤍🖤 I’m thrilled to announce that I’m officially a part of #SephoraSquad2023 🎉

All of your beautiful and heartfelt testimonials got me into this exclusive one year program! I’m honored to be chosen out of the thousands that have applied and I can’t wait to meet my fellow Squad members. 

I started my passion in beauty when I was 16 at Sephora Inside JCPenney. When I turned 19 I realized that I wanted to go to school for nursing and worked at a nursing home for a year. The pandemic hit and I started content just like everyone else. That same year my mom was diagnosed with stage 4 cancer and I stopped everything. But, she always wanted me to pursue content and supported that more than nursing lol When she passed in 2021 I found my way back to creating content as a way to cope with such deep grief. 2022 I was all in and took content full time which grew my platforms immensely, but it was hard financially. I decided 2023 to go back to Sephora to gain insight of clients needs are so I can make content that connected to THEIR needs. Real everyday people. Also I missed just that 101 connection on how I can help someone with their beauty needs. 

I know my purpose is to help people. Maybe it’s not to help them in the medical field, but to help their inner/outer beauty. I’ve embraced the skill set that I have instead of the traditional route. 

Break the chain. Become the entrepreneur even when no one thinks it’s possible. No one can be you.
Thank you to my family, friends, and especially my man for supporting me through my highest highs and lowest lows. For loving me no matter what.
Thank you to my mommy for being the best mommy anyone could ask for, my angel in heaven guiding me and protecting me.
Thank you to @sephora & @fohr.co for believing in me and choosing me to be a part of this amazing opportunity.
Thank you to the man above, mama mary and Ate for blessing me everyday.
Thank YOU for supporting me and helping me get to where I am. For putting your trust in my beauty tips and food reviews lol 
I’ve shared my journey with you and I’m so excited to bring you along for this next one 🫶🏼

I love you and a million times thank you,

Ray ♡

a dream come true @sephorasquad 🤍🖤 #SephoraSquad2023 

i started off this trip super excited yet nervous. literally so afraid to come out my shell and mingle. as time went on this glam turtle 🐢 came out the shell and bloomed into a social butterfly 🦋 . despite all the wonderful gifting, meeting @patrickta , and chatting with @selenagomez on zoom.. (super grateful for all of these things) the most valuable part of this trip is how much i’ve learned from my fellow squad members and the friendships that i’ve gained. that was absolutely priceless. 

there is no school or degree for what we do as creators and to be surrounded by so many.. the energy was beautiful. you realize that you aren’t alone and there is a whole room of people who understands exactly what you go through. listening to all the different stories, backgrounds, and advice you can’t help but to absorb it all.

i wish i got more pictures with everyone. 

also huge thank you to @taskyourself for all your wisdom you have blessed myself and many other squad members throughout the entire trip 🤍 you truly are a gem!! 

this was also my first trip alone which was honestly very relaxing and highly encourage everyone to do once because you learn alot about yourself.

thank you @sephorasquad @sephora @fohr.co for believing in me when i had doubt in myself and giving me this incredible experience. there was definitely magic in the air because i left more confident in myself and in my purpose as a creator 🤍🖤

so much love and ENDLESS hugs since the moment we arrived.

can you believe this is just the beginning?! so excited to see the squad again and continue this beautiful journey with you all ❤️

with love,

Ray

11.20 🕊️🤍 you would have been 48…

i sit here watching this video wondering what you wished for. 

it absolutely kills me not knowing what it was. 

this was your last birthday we shared with you on earth.

i talk to you all the time in my prayers, but oh how much i miss your voice. your laugh. 

if you know my mom she really isn’t like the sentimental type so i’m sure she is like laughing why are you crying and typing all this lmao 

but she loved so hard. especially us kids.

i want you all to know that even though in this photo she was in so much pain.. she smiled the whole time and was so happy.

my mom is strength in human form. 

on this day every year we will celebrate the amazing life of my mom. how she was the best mom anyone could ever have. 

the pieces of her spirit on earth are within my siblings and i. 

a Queen was born on this day. 
her legacy is everlasting. 
her beautiful soul lives forever in Heaven.

Happy Birthday Mommy 🤍 I love and miss you more than words could ever describe.
